/phdmah.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/2cc0055832264c5296890745e9ea415c|accessdate=15 April 2020}}</ref>\n| fatality_rate =\n| territories = Pune city, Pimpri, Chinchwad and rural areas of Pune\n| total_ili =\n| website = [https://arogya.maharashtra.gov.in/1175/Novel--Corona-Virus arogya.maharashtra.gov.in]\n            [https://phdmah.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/2cc0055832264c5296890745e9ea415c Public Health Department, Maharashtra]\n}}\n\nThe first cases of the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] were confirmed in [[Pune]] on 9 March 2020. These were the first two cases in the state of [[Maharashtra]]. This article refers to [[Pune district]], which includes the municipal corporations of Pune and Pimpri-Chinchwad, as well as rural areas of Pune. Pune has confirmed a total of 351 (including 35 death and 39 recoveries), as of 15 April 2020.\n__TOC__\n\n=='''Background'''==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in [[Wuhan City]], Hubei Province, [[China]], which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.\n\nThe case fatality ratio for [[COVID-19]] has been much lower than [[SARS]] of 2003,but the transmission has been significantly greater, with a significant totl death toll.\n\n=='''Timeline'''==\n{{Medical cases chart\n|barwidth   = wide\n|numwidth   = mwtw\n|float      = \n|pretitle   = \n|disease    = COVID-19\n|location   = Pune\n|location2  = Maharashtra\n|location3  = India\n|outbreak   = 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic\n|recoveries = y\n|right1= Confirmed cases\n|divisor    = \n|collapsible= \n|rows=\n{{Medical cases chart/Row|2020-03-09|0|0|2|||2|+2|||factor=0.3|numwidth=mwtw}}\n{{Medical cases chart/Row|2020-03-10|0|0|5|||5|+3|||factor=0.3|numwidth=mwtw}}\n{{Medical cases chart/Row|2020-03-11|0|0|8|||8|+3|||factor=0.3|numwidth=mwtw}}\n{{Medical cases chart/Row|2020-03-12|0|0|8|||8|+0|||factor=0.3|